    "description": {
      "value": "<h2><span class=\"fontstyle0\">COMPELLING DIRECTIVE</span></h2>\n<p style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\">At 4</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"font-size: 6pt;\">th&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">level, you can increase one ability score of your choice by 1. You canâ€™t increase an ability score above 20 using this feature except for your primary born leader ability, which has a maximum value of 22.</span></p>\n<p style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\">Additionally, after you finish a long rest, roll a d20 and put the result aside. You can swap out any roll you or an ally that can communicate with you makes for that result. You should always have a d20 result put aside this way, but after swapping two die rolls, you cannot swap another until you finish a short or long rest. After you finish a long rest, you always roll a new d20.</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>",
